<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E32FFC4462EE1AE83DDFD1F" box="[836,907,661,687]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Brasil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E32FFC446F0E1AE83AEFD1F" box="[922,1016,661,687]" name="Canada" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Canada</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="03FB763B6E32FFC4416DE1AE841FFD1F" box="[1031,1097,661,687]" name="Israel" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Israel</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E32FFC44131E1AE80BAFD7F" author="Kanneby T." pageId="3" pageNumber="352" pagination="29 - 55" refId="ref3742" refString="Kanneby T. 2011. New species and new records of freshwater Chaetonotida (Gastrotricha) from Sweden. Zootaxa, 3115, 29 - 55." type="journal article" year="2011">Kånneby, 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Typical periphytyc species for olygo- and mesosaprobic water bodies (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E32FFC44135E18E80BAFD5F" author="Sladecek, V." pageId="3" pageNumber="352" refId="ref4033" refString="Sladecek, V. 1976. Indicator value of freshwater Gastrotricha. Acta hydrochim. hydrobiol., 4" type="book" year="1976">Sladeček, 1976</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7B5336AB6E32FFC44589E1CE843AFC9F" blockId="3.[174,1233,308,815]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">
Remarks. More than century ago this species is reported from Ukrainian Carpathians (
<bibRefCitation id="1F7D4B5A6E32FFC44586E02E81CBFC9F" author="Jakubski, A. W." box="[236,413,789,815]" pageId="3" pageNumber="352" pagination="20 - 42" refId="ref3711" refString="Jakubski, A. W. 1919. Fauna wrotkow (Rotatoria) i brzuchorzeskow (Gastrotricha) Stawu Grodeckiego i okolicy. Kosmos, 43, 20 - 42." type="journal article" year="1919">Jakubski, 1919</bibRefCitation>
). This species is reported in 
<collectingRegion id="B928F8496E32FFC4478CE02E83C8FC9F" box="[742,926,789,815]" country="Ukraine" name="Kharkiv" pageId="3" pageNumber="352">Kharkiv Region</collectingRegion>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
